tags.name: Sammo Senior High School, Cape Coast

tags.description: University Practice Senior High, located on the University of Cape Coast (UCC) campus, was established in October 1979 as a practice centre for the Faculty of Education of the University.
tags.name: University Practice Senior High School
Rev. Alec Jones Memorial Methodist School
Kwaprow School, Primary and Junior High
Kwaprow School, Primary and Junior High

tags.description: The school was originally established as a private community school in 1991 at Abrem Agona Catholic J.S.S. and is located in the Komenda-Edina-Eguafo- Abrem municipality, North West of Elmina.
tags.name: Eguafo-Abrem Senior High School

tags.description: The 2007 Education Reforms transmuted the curriculum of the institute with the integration of the core subjects. The Programmes currently are run at the COTVET Certificate II level.
tags.name: Asuansi Technical Institute

tags.description: Ghana National College was the first school established by Dr. Kwame Nkrumah. It is located on Menya Menwu Hills in Cape Coast.
tags.name: Ghana National College

tags.description: Jukwa Senior High School is a co-educational public school and has both day and boarding facilities. It is among the school selected for SEIP scholarship and has an average WASSCE pass rate.
tags.name: Jukwa Senior High School

tags.description: St. Augustine’s College started at Amissano, a village near Elmina, in 1930. The Roman Catholic institution was established to serve as a training college and seminary. The school was named after St. Augustine of Hippo (354 -430).
tags.name: St. Augustine's College

tags.description: Abakrampa Senior High Technical School was established in January, 1991. This was in fulfilment of the PNDC ACT 207, which instituted Senior Secondary Schools as a followup to the new educational reforms of 1987.
tags.name: Abakrampa Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: Academy of Christ the King SHS was founded on 15th October, 1976 by the Mothers’ Union of the Anglican Church, Cape Coast under the leadership of the Most Rev. I. S. M. Le-Maire and the Most Rev. R.G.A. Okine
tags.name: Academy of Christ The King

tags.description: Adisadel College was founded on January 4th 1910 by the Society for the Propagation of the Gospel and is situated on a hill a few miles north of Cape Coast, Ghana, with breathtaking views of the Atlantic Ocean.
tags.name: Adisadel College

tags.description: The school is located on the Cape Coast-Takoradi highway, Aggrey Memorial has two sites separated by a road; the girls’ site is linked to the boys’ site by an overhead bridge.
tags.name: Aggrey Memorial A.M.E. Zion Senior High School

tags.description: The School was founded by the Late Joseph Kadesh Abraham in 1955. It was originally called The College of Architecture and has undergone various change of names until in 1976 when the Ghana Government absorbed it into the public system
tags.name: Cape Coast Technical Institute

tags.description: The Edinaman Senior High School, formerly Edinaman Day School, was established on 9th January, 1978 at Elmina Castle. The school moved to its current location, the Paul Isert Hill in 1992.
tags.name: Edinaman Senior High School

tags.description: Efutu Senior High Technical School, originally established as a Community Day School in February 1999, was later absorbed into the Public Educational System by the Government through the Ghana Education Service in September 2001.
tags.name: Effutu Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: Komenda Senior High/Technical School was established by the Government of Ghana in accordance with PNDC Law 207 as a community, co-educational and day institution in January, 1991.
tags.name: Komenda Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: Mfantsipim is a Methodist secondary school in Cape Coast, Ghana. It is the first secondary school to be established in the Gold Coast, (now Ghana) as Wesleyan High School, founded on 3 April 1876.
tags.name: Mfantsipim Senior High School

tags.description: Oguaa Senior High Technical School is located between the Holy Child School and the Aggrey Memorial Senior High School.
tags.name: Oguaa Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: A government assisted girls’ Methodist school with a strong Methodist tradition. Founded, in 1836 by the wife of the second Methodist missionary to the Gold Coast, Mrs. Harriet Wrigley.
tags.name: Wesley Girls Senior High School
